article.headline: Hampton 70, William &amp, Mary 63
article.story: HAMPTON, Va. (AP) -- Rashad West scored 29 points, including 18 in the second half, and Hampton held off a late rally to beat William & Mary 70-63 on Saturday night. Jordan Brooks scored 12 points and Michael Freeman added 11 for the Pirates (6-6), who took a 54-33 lead with 7:42 remaining on Brooks' 3-pointer. The Tribe (3-7) began chipping away at the lead and Kyle Carrabine hit a 3-pointer with 11 seconds remaining to cut the lead to three. They could get no closer. David Schneider and Danny Sumner scored 14 points apiece for William & Mary. The Tribe shot 3-of-20 from 3-point range in the loss.
